1 SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2063e of Title 63, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 The State Commissioner of Health shall promulgate rules
5 necessary to implement this act including, but not limited to, rules
6 that:
7 1. Adopt a set of standards for the approval of certified
8 community health worker initial coursework or curriculum;
9 2. Establish examination administration requirements for the
10 State Department of Health or one or more designees;
11 3. Define minimum qualifications for applicants to be
12 certified; provided, however, the applicant shall be exempt from any
13 educational, training, or examination requirements if the applicant
14 has provided evidence to the State Department of Health of work
15 experience as a community health worker demonstrating a minimum of
16 one thousand (1,000) practical hours and a recommendation from a
17 supervising provider;
18 4. Establish the criteria for granting, renewing, denying,
19 suspending, and revoking a certificate to uphold health standards
20 and safety;
21 5. Prescribe fees for the certified community health worker
22 examination, initial certification, and certification renewal; and
23
24
